{
  "texts": [
    "Conceptual schema views: a set of views that define a one-to-one mapping of the relational schema to end users' terms; the views basically rename tables and columns.",
    "Figure 6.2 shows the referential dependencies diagram of a much- simplified version of the conceptual schema views, where an arrow represents a foreign key and points to the referenced table, as usual.",
    "Partially extended views: a set of views that extend the conceptual schema views with new columns that predefine joins that follow foreign keys, as well as other selected columns.",
    "Figure 6.3 shows that previously it was necessary to have at least three joins between the Installation and Maintenance_Order tables.",
    "Creating an installation_id column in Mainte-nance_Order, reduced it to just one join between the tables."
  ]
}